<HEAD>Separatist Group Blows Up Tourist Complex</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CALVI, Corsica (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Masked men set off explosives that destroyed 80 apartments under construction in a tourist complex, police said. The separatist <ORGANIZATION> Corsican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Front </ORGANIZATION> claimed responsibility. Police said two men wearing hoods tied up 11 people living at the site, mostly construction workers, and drove them to a village 15 miles away before detonating the blast early Monday in the apartment complex in <LOCATION> Calvi </LOCATION> on the northwestern coast of this French Mediterranean island. No injuries were reported. The <ORGANIZATION> Corsican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Front </ORGANIZATION> claimed responsibility in a statement made public in the <LOCATION> Bastia </LOCATION>, the nearest major city, saying it was fighting `` speculative enterprises which will lead eventually to the marginalization of our people on their own land.'' A similar attack last month destroyed 135 apartments under construction at <LOCATION> Santa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lucia </LOCATION> di <ORGANIZATION> Porto </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Vecchio </ORGANIZATION> in southeastern <LOCATION> Corsica </LOCATION>.
