ey may be sent an explanation of the suit and a form seeking their consent to join the court fight. The form said the judge authorized the mailing but took no position on the merits of the case. An increased number of plaintiffs in such suits can be a big advantage for the workers because it spreads out court costs. In seeking workers to join the suit, the leaders of the court fight asked, but did not require, a $ 200 contribution to help defray the costs. The <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> today upheld a ruling by the 3rd <LOCATION> U.S </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Circuit </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Appeals </ORGANIZATION>. The case is <PERSON> Hoffmann-La </PERSON> <PERSON> Roche </PERSON> vs. <PERSON> Sperling </PERSON>, 88-1203.
