<BYLINE>By BARRY SCHWEID</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Diplomatic Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WEST BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Secretary of State <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Baker </PERSON> <PERSON> III </PERSON> cautioned West German leaders Monday that they alone can not decide the pace of reunification with <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Baker </PERSON> flew here for talks with Chancellor <PERSON> Helmut </PERSON> <PERSON> Kohl </PERSON> and Foreign Minister <PERSON> Hans-Dietrich </PERSON> <PERSON> Genscher </PERSON> and a visit to the now-porous <LOCATION> Berlin </LOCATION> Wall after a stop in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>. There he reaffirmed a special <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> relationship with the government of Prime Minister <PERSON> Marager </PERSON> <PERSON> Thatcher </PERSON> and said he did not believe the two close allies were drifting apart. `` I do n't think there are any fences that need mending,'' <PERSON> Baker </PERSON> said after a 50-minute conversation with Mrs. <PERSON> Thatcher </PERSON> at No. 10 Downing St. `` We feel a special relation to the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Kingdom </LOCATION> and to the prime minister.'' He said there had been `` some minsuderstanding'' of President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>'s call at a meeting of <ORGANIZATION> NATO </ORGANIZATION> leaders on Dec. 4 in <LOCATION> Brussels </LOCATION> for `` perhaps even an intensified effort'' at economic and political integration of <LOCATION> Western </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>. Mrs. <PERSON> Thatcher </PERSON> has resisted most moves in that direction, but gone along reluctantly. Overriding her objections, the <ORGANIZATION> European </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Community </ORGANIZATION> on Saturday made steps toward creating a central bank and a common currency for the 12-nation region. `` I do n't think the differences were as real as they were portrayed in the British press,'' <PERSON> Baker </PERSON> told reporters later as he flew to <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Berlin </LOCATION>. Be