ith 850 inmates, were severely damaged by fires, <ORGANIZATION> PAP </ORGANIZATION> said. Rioting also was suppressed at the <PERSON> Kaminski </PERSON> penitentirary that houses about 1,000 inmates. <PERSON> Laminski </PERSON> told <ORGANIZATION> PAP </ORGANIZATION> that 800 Czarne inmates were transferred to other prisons. All four prisons are maximum security facilities. About 17,000 prisoners were expected to benefit from the amnesty program approved by the <ORGANIZATION> Sejm </ORGANIZATION> but it was not applied to those with four or more convictions.
