at they must focus on costs, customers and competitors.'' Most of this year's cuts have come through early retirement or attrition, but several thousand have come through unannounced cuts. Since 1984 when the company divested its regional operating companies, <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> T </ORGANIZATION> has cut about 90,000 jobs. The company will have a payroll of about 280,000 employees by January.
