<HEAD>For Release in Yearend Editions</HEAD>
<HEAD>Poll on Economic Issues has 1,117 Respondents</HEAD>
<HEAD>With BC-Decade-Poll</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 This <ORGANIZATION> Media </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> General-Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> poll is based on telephone interviews Nov. 17-25 with 1,117 adults in the continental <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. Phone numbers were selected randomly and interviews were conducted with the adult who had the most recent birthday, a random phenomenon. The results were weighted to adjust for variations in the sample. The poll has a 3-point margin of error, meaning that 19 of 20 times its findings should be within 3 points of the result if every adult American were asked the same questions. The error margin is larger for subgroups. There are other sources of potential error in polls, including the wording and order of questions. These are the questions in this poll; because of rounding, sums may not total 100: 1a. In your opinion, which country is the world's leading economic power right now _ the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>, the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> or some other country? <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION>: 26 percent. <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>: 68 percent. <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>: 1 percent. <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION>: 1. Other: 0. Do n't know or no answer: 4. -LRB- if <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> -RRB- Do you think the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> will remain the world's leading economic power during the next 10 years, or not? Yes: 71. No: 17. DK-NA: 11. 2. Do you think the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>' economic leadership has strengthened during the last 10 years, gotten weaker, or remained at about the same level? Strengthened: 16. Weaker: 56. Same: 26. DK-NA: 3. 3. Do you think the federal government should help finance new industries it wants to develop, or should it let market forces determine which industries get established? Government: 37. Market: 51. DK-NA: 13. 4. Compared to 10 years ago, is your family's financial situation better today, or worse today, or about the same? Better: 52. Worse: 18. Same: 28. DK-NA: 2. 5. In the next 10 years, do you expect your family's financial situation to get better, or worse, or remain about the same? Better: 49. Worse: 13. Same: 34. DK-NA: 4. 6. For each of the following, please tell me if you think it's been good or bad for the nation's economy in the last 10 years, or if it has n't made much difference: a Corporate mergers. Good: 20. Bad: 51. No difference: 20. DK-NA: 10. b Government deregulation. Good: 35. Bad: 34. No difference: 15. DK-NA: 17. c. The stock market Good: 29. Bad: 26. No difference: 27. DK-NA: 19. d. More women in the work force Good: 77. Bad: 11. No difference: 9. DK-NA: 4. e. The federal deficit Good: 5. Bad: 78. No difference: 10. DK-NA: 7. f. Competition from foreign imports Good: 20. Bad: 68. No difference: 6. DK-NA: 6. g. Foreign investment in the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Good: 24 Bad: 59. No difference: 8. DK-NA: 9.
