<HEAD>Home Shopping Network Announces Record Sales, Income</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Shopping </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Network </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> on Monday announced record sales and earnings for the quarter ended Nov. 30, including an 85 percent increase in profit. The results represent a turnaround for the electronic retailer, which sells products through a television show shown on cable TV networks. <ORGANIZATION> HSN </ORGANIZATION> lost $ 26.1 million in the quarter ended Aug. 31, and lost $ 14.9 million for the fiscal year that ended that date. For the most recent quarter, net income grew to $ 20.2 million, or 21 cents per share, from the $ 10.9 million, or 12 cents a share, for the same period last year, the company said. Sales for the quarter were a record $ 255.2 million. That was up 27.2 percent from the $ 200.6 million reported for the same period last year, the company said. `` The solid gains <ORGANIZATION> HSN </ORGANIZATION> has reported in the first quarter reinforce our decision to focus the company's resources to its core business, electronic retailing,'' said <PERSON> Roy </PERSON> <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> Speer </PERSON>, chairman and chief executive officer. The retailing firm has streamlined its operations, <PERSON> Speer </PERSON> said, and has `` significantly curtailed or eliminated activities that did not provide adequate returns on our investments.''
