PERSON> <PERSON> Cook </PERSON> <PERSON> Travel </PERSON>, based in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, operates from about 150 locations and had sales of about $ 650 million last year, <PERSON> Paresky </PERSON> said. A spokesman for <ORGANIZATION> Crimson </ORGANIZATION> said the new operation, which will be the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> member of the multinational <ORGANIZATION> Thomas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cook </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> network based in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>, will be the third-largest <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> travel company, following those operated by <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Express </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Carlson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cos. </ORGANIZATION>' Ask Mr. <PERSON> Foster </PERSON> `` We have created a company with the leadership and resources to provide our customers with unequaled global travel service,'' <PERSON> Maxwell </PERSON> said in a statement.
